==English==

===Noun===
'''diff'''
#(''slang'') Shortened form of [[difference]]
#:''A peach and an apricot? What's the diff?''

===Transitive Verb===
#(''computing'') To run a diff program.
#(''computing'') To produce a description of changes made to a collection of files.  To produce a [[patch file]].

===Proper noun===
#(''computing'') A program, historically associated with the [[Unix]] [[operating system]], which compares two files or sets of files an outputs a description of the differences between them.
#(''computing'') The output of a diff program.  A [[diff file]].

